  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some good figure skating songs?",
  "response": "Choosing the right music for a figure skating program is crucial as it needs to complement the skater\u2019s style, emphasize their strengths, and engage the audience. Here are some popular and effective choices, spanning various genres:\n\n### Classical and Orchestral\n1. **\"Swan Lake\"** by Pyotr Ilyich Tchaikovsky\n2. **\"Carmen\"** by Georges Bizet\n3. **\"Rhapsody in Blue\"** by George Gershwin\n4. **\"Nutcracker Suite\"** by Pyotr Ilyich Tchaikovsky\n5. **\"Adagio for Strings\"** by Samuel Barber\n\n### Instrumental\n1. **\"Claire de Lune\"** by Claude Debussy\n2. **\"Winter\" from The Four Seasons by Antonio Vivaldi**\n3. **\"Bol\u00e9ro\"** by Maurice Ravel\n4. **\"Turandot: Nessun Dorma\"** by Giacomo Puccini\n\n### Contemporary and Pop\n1. **\"Shallow\"** by Lady Gaga and Bradley Cooper\n2. **\"A Thousand Years\"** by Christina Perri\n3. **\"Halo\"** by Beyonc\u00e9\n4. **\"Someone You Loved\"** by Lewis Capaldi\n\n### Soundtracks and Musicals\n1. **\"My Heart Will Go On\"** from Titanic\n2. **\"The Greatest Show\"** from The Greatest Showman\n3. **\"Let It Go\"** from Frozen\n4. **\"This Is Me\"** from The Greatest Showman\n5. **\"I Dreamed a Dream\"** from Les Mis\u00e9rables\n6. **\"Once Upon a Time in America\"** by Ennio Morricone\n\n### Jazz and Blues\n1. **\"Fever\"** by Peggy Lee\n2. **\"At Last\"** by Etta James\n3. **\"Fly Me to the Moon\"** by Frank Sinatra\n\n### Rock and Alternative\n1. **\"Bohemian Rhapsody\"** by Queen\n2. **\"November Rain\"** by Guns N' Roses\n3. **\"Hallelujah\"** by Jeff Buckley\n\nSkaters often choose music that not only resonates with them but also highlights their technical abilities and artistic expression. Keep in mind the length of the piece and how the tempo and mood transitions suit the choreography.",
